How to Change Docker’s Default Data Directory
如何更改 Docker 的預設資料目錄

No more room for your deployments? Here's a quick guide to relocating Docker's storage path for images, volumes, containers, etc.
  • ByBobby Borisov
  • OnMay 26, 2024

Running out of disk space is one of the most common issues users face. When using containerized Docker services, reaching that point means that your deployments will stop working. This happens for one simple reason—your Linux system becomes unable to execute any further write operations on the disk.
磁碟空間不足是用戶面臨的最常見問題之一。使用容器化 Docker 服務時，達到該點意味著您的部署將停止工作。發生這種情況的原因很簡單 — 您的 Linux 系統無法在磁碟上執行任何進一步的寫入作。

Fortunately, there’s a practical solution. This article will guide you through the steps to relocate Docker’s storage path for images, volumes, containers, etc., ensuring that your projects continue smoothly without the hassle of disk space limitations.
幸運的是，有一個實用的解決方案。本文將指導您完成重新定位 Docker 的鏡像、卷、容器等存儲路徑的步驟，確保您的專案順利進行，而不會受到磁碟空間限制的困擾。

To clarify things, consider this: our disk is 99% full, dangerously close to rendering our entire Linux system inoperable. We’ve added a new 100GB disk to handle this unpleasant situation and mounted it as the “/data” directory in our filesystem.
為了澄清事情，請考慮一下：我們的磁碟已經滿了99%，危險地接近於使我們的整個Linux系統無法運行。我們加入了一個新的 100GB 磁碟來處理這種令人不快的情況，並將其作為 “/data” 目錄掛載到我們的檔案系統中。

We plan to move all Docker resources to this location, which frees up significant space on the “/” root partition. This will ensure that not only Docker but also our Linux system as a whole continues to operate without any hiccups.
我們計劃將所有 Docker 資源移動到此位置，從而釋放 「根分區上的大量空間」。這將確保 Docker 和我們的整個 Linux 系統繼續運行而不會出現任何問題。

Step 1: Stop Docker Service
步驟 1：停止 Docker 服務

Before making any changes, ensure all your containers are stopped, and Docker is not running. You can do this using the following commands:
在進行任何更改之前，請確保您的所有容器都已停止，並且 Docker 未運行。您可以使用以下命令執行此作：

sudo systemctl stop docker.service
sudo systemctl stop docker.socketCode language: Bash (bash)

Of course, remember that this will cause all your Docker containers to shut down, so downtime is inevitable.
當然，請記住，這將導致所有 Docker 容器關閉，因此停機是不可避免的。

Step 2: Move the Docker’s Data Directory
步驟 2：移動 Docker 的數據目錄

Docker stores all its data in a default directory, including images, containers, volumes, and networks. On most Linux systems, this is typically “/var/lib/docker.” While this works well for initial setups, as the number of projects grows, so does the data.
Docker 將其所有數據儲存在預設目錄中，包括映像、容器、卷和網路。在大多數 Linux 系統上，這通常是 “/var/lib/docker”。雖然這適用於初始設置，但隨著項目數量的增加，數據也會增加。

Because of this, the next step is to move the existing Docker directory to a new location with more disk space, which, in our case, is the “/data” directory. Let’s first create a subdirectory for it, for example, “docker,” where we plan to relocate and store our Docker data going forward.
因此，下一步是將現有的 Docker 目錄移動到具有更多磁碟空間的新位置，在我們的例子中，該位置是“/data”目錄。讓我們首先為它創建一個子目錄，例如“docker”，我們計劃在其中重新定位和存儲我們的 Docker 數據。

sudo mkdir /data/dockerCode language: Bash (bash)

It’s time to get to action. While you could use the recursive cp command or even mv to transfer data, we advise against this. Instead, the safest and most reliable method is the rsync command. If it isn’t already available on your Linux distro, you can easily add it by installing the “rsync” package through your package manager.
是時候採取行動了。雖然你可以使用遞歸 cp 命令，甚至 mv 傳輸數據，但我們建議不要這樣做。相反，最安全、最可靠的方法是命令 rsync 。如果您的 Linux 發行版上尚不可用，您可以通過包管理器安裝 “rsync” 包來輕鬆加入它。

To copy all data from the “/var/lib/docker” to the “/data/docker” directory, we execute the command below, as the first argument is the source directory, and the second is the destination.
要將所有數據從“/var/lib/docker”複製到“/data/docker”目錄，我們執行以下命令，因為第一個參數是源目錄，第二個參數是目標目錄。

sudo rsync -aP /var/lib/docker/ /data/docker/Code language: Bash (bash)

Okay, what does this command do? The “-a” (archive mode) option permits recursive file copying while preserving all symbolic links, file permissions, user and group ownership, and timestamps. The “-P” option keeps partially transferred files if the transfer interrupts. It also shows the transfer progress for each file being copied.
好的，這個命令是做什麼的呢？“-a”（存檔模式）選項允許遞歸檔複製，同時保留所有符號鏈接、檔案許可權、使用者和組擁有權以及時間戳。如果傳輸中斷，“-P” 選項會保留部分傳輸的檔。它還顯示正在複製的每個檔案的傳輸進度。

For more in-depth information about the rsync command, visit our comprehensive guide, “Rsync Command in Linux with Practical Examples.”
有關該 rsync 命令的更深入資訊，請訪問我們的綜合指南“Linux 中的 Rsync 命令與實際示例”。

Step 3: Update the Docker Configuration
第 3 步：更新 Docker 組態

After copying the data, you must tell Docker where to find its new home. This can be done by editing the special Docker configuration file, “daemon.json,” in the “/etc/docker” directory.
複製數據後，您必須告訴 Docker 在哪裡可以找到它的新家。這可以通過編輯 “/etc/docker” 目錄中的特殊 Docker 組態檔 “daemon.json” 來完成。

Note that a Docker installation doesn’t automatically create this file, so if you have not done any manual configurations before, it’s normal for the file to be missing. If that’s the case, create it and put it in the snippet below. Of course, remember to replace “/new/docker/root” with the appropriate filesystem path for your setup.
請注意，Docker 安裝不會自動創建此檔，因此如果您之前沒有進行任何手動組態，則缺少該檔是正常的。如果是這種情況，請創建它並將其放在下面的代碼段中。當然，請記住將 「/new/docker/root」 替換為適合您設置的檔案系統路徑。

sudo nano /etc/docker/daemon.jsonCode language: Bash (bash)
{ 
   "data-root": "/new/docker/root"
}Code language: JSON / JSON with Comments (json)

Finally, save the file and exit.
最後，保存檔並退出。

Step 4: Start Docker & Verify the New Setup
步驟4：啟動Docker並驗證新設置

Okay, the moment of truth. Start the Docker service:
好的，關鍵時刻。啟動 Docker 服務：

sudo systemctl start docker.socket
sudo systemctl start docker.serviceCode language: Bash (bash)

Make sure the Docker service has started up smoothly and is fully operational.
確保 Docker 服務已順利啟動並完全運行。

sudo systemctl status dockerCode language: Bash (bash)

Finally, ensure that Docker is using the directory we specified for data storage as its default:
最後，確保 Docker 使用我們為資料儲存指定的目錄作為其預設目錄：

sudo docker info | grep "Docker Root Dir"Code language: Bash (bash)

This should display the new path, confirming that the relocation was successful.
這應該會顯示新路徑，確認重定位成功。

Post-installation Steps  安裝後步驟

Ensure that all your Docker containers are functioning as expected. If they are not set to start automatically, run them manually one at a time and check for any irregularities in their operation.
確保所有 Docker 容器都按預期運行。如果它們未設置為自動啟動，請一次手動運行一個，並檢查其作中是否有任何異常情況。

Only after you have verified that everything is running smoothly can you proceed to free up disk space by removing the directory previously used by Docker to store data.
只有在驗證一切運行順暢後，才能通過刪除 Docker 以前用於存儲資料的目錄來釋放磁碟空間。

sudo rm -rf /var/lib/docker/Code language: Bash (bash)

Bottom Line  底線

Relocating Docker’s storage path is a straightforward process that can significantly alleviate disk space constraints, allowing you to scale your projects. This ensures the continued smooth operation of your Dockerized services and prevents your Linux system from becoming inoperable due to a lack of disk space.
重新置放 Docker 的儲存路徑是一個簡單的過程，可以顯著緩解磁碟空間限制，從而允許您擴展專案。這可確保您的 Docker 化服務持續平穩運行，並防止您的 Linux 系統因磁碟空間不足而無法運行。

We also want to mention that you can modify systemd’s Docker service to achieve the same result instead of changing the “daemon.json” file. However, we consider this approach a workaround rather than a proper solution, and we don’t recommend it, so we don’t cover it in our guide.
我們還想提一下，你可以修改 systemd 的 Docker 服務來達到相同的結果，而不是更改 「daemon.json」 檔。但是，我們認為這種方法是一種解決方法，而不是適當的解決方案，因此我們不建議這樣做，因此我們不會在指南中介紹它。

Refer to the official documentation for more detailed information on configuring Docker using the “daemon.json” file.

We’re grateful for your use of this guide and hope it has made the process clear and manageable. We value your feedback and comments, so please feel free to share them in the section below. Happy deploying!
